{
  "stem": "12413.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't-- if I recall my-- not childhood; I was 12-- I liked to-- I didn't like to, you know, to get like orders, and the ideas to be imposed on me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was a free thinker to a certain extent, if I can say this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Polish.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think the parents spoke between the Yiddish, which we didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think my brother understood a little Yiddish, much more than myself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I didn't know Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I was home, I don't recall.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when they spoke sometimes between them Yiddish, just for one reason, we should not understand what they want to say.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they used Yiddish language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But Polish was the spoken language.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean the community in my town?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You mean by how many Jews are living in the?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Czestochowa had about 120,000 inhabitants, 30,000-- over 30,000 Jews, and 90,000 Poles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The city was, I would say, very anti-Semitic, very, very, very, very much.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even in normal times before the war-- I am talking about 1937 and 1938-- the Poles were smashing windows in Jewish stores or carrying anti-Semitic slogans, which they say, Jews to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have-- I have Polish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have Polish friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, I have Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maybe my Aryan appearance-- I was blonde with blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I was well accepted, you know, by the Poles, calling me, they would say, [NON-ENGLISH]-- a good Jew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Czestochowa is a historical city known for the famous Shrine of Matka Boska-- the Black Madonna-- which is comparable to the Lady of Guadalupe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Every year, pilgrims by thousand used to swarm to this town, walking on their knees, bleeding to reach this sacred place of this town.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Even the Pope,  I think, every year pays a visit to this place, because it's very known.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
